Police at Ngqeleni near Mthatha have arrested two men aged 36 and 50 after they were found in possession of several unlicensed firearms and ammunition, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. The suspects were arrested by Ngqeleni police and national inteverntion unit (NIU) [officers] from Mthatha during an operation that was conducted at Nkumandeni locality in Ngqeleni, police said in a statement on the South African Police Service (SAPS) official Facebook page. The operation commenced at midnight [on Friday] and ended today [Saturday] at about 4am. The two arrested men would appear in the Ngqeleni Magistrate s Court on Monday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition.